Rating: 3
We loved this lamb dish. I made a couple of changes. I added one tbl honey to the marinade. I drained the marinade off and rolled the medallions in seasoned breadcrumbs and flour. I then sauteed these in a frypan with some good olive oil. Set the meat aside and I made a sauce/gravy from a rich lamb stock (roast the lamb bones, add beef boullion,red or white wine, rosemary, garlic and salt and simmer for one hour and strain the stock) added a little flour, rosemary salt and pepper and served over the lamb. It was wonderful.

Rating: 3
This dish is very tasty, and quite easy too. The marinade adds a wonderful flavor. In the future, I may not even add the bread crumbs, and just let the marinade do its work. Had a little problem with the broiler....maybe will try grilling next time, or pan-searing and then baking. The breadcrumbs browned too quickly under the broiler, even after repositioning the racks. Still, the flavor and ease of preparation was well worth the broiling fiasco.